==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waistcoateer
<hw>Waist`coat*eer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One wearing a
waistcoat; esp., a woman wearing one uncovered, or thought fit for such
a habit; hence, a loose woman; strumpet.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Do you think you are here, sir,⟦br⟧
Amongst your <qex>waistcoateers</qex>, your base wenches?</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waistcoating</ent>⟦br⟧
